ng to the side, thy graces noting;"],["But since she prick'd thee out for women's pleasure,","I bow and give everything to thy pleasure"],["Mine be thy love and thy love's use their treasure.","And add these lines to all thy gathered treasure."]],[["So is it not with me as with that Muse","Like lecher poet with a saucy muse,"],["Stirr'd by a painted beauty to his verse,","I lustfully my bawdy lines rehearse"],["Who heaven itself for ornament doth use","I'll not my sordid mistress rhymes refuse"],["And every fair with his fair doth rehearse","And cause the jealous to turn green and curse"],["Making a couplement of proud compare,","And e'en when thou art laid by Nature bare"],["With sun and moon, with earth and sea's rich gems,","Thy beauties shine and one compares those gems"],["With April's first-born flowers, and all things rare","With treasures locked by miser.  One may dare"],["That heaven's air in this huge rondure hems.","See danger in the darkness when sun dims"],["O' let me, true in love, but truly write,","And all is lit with an eerie twilight;"],["And then believe me, my love is as fair","Of thy soft tresses and thy eyes so fair"],["As any mother's child, though not so bright","I praise thy timeless beauty in the light"],["As those gold candles fix'd in heaven's air:","Distracted though I be by bosom bare"],["Let them say more than like of hearsay well;","When of thy virtues all I seek to tell"],["I will not praise that purpose not to sell.","I find a full and o'erbrimming well"]],[["My glass shall not persuade me I am old,","I think not that you ever shall grow old"],["So long as youth and thou are of one date;","As long as you appear so fair of late"],["But when in thee time's furrows I behold,","To think you unpreserv'd I feel then bold;"],["Then look I death my days should expiate.","'Tis only then that I should fear my fate"],["For all that beauty that doth cover thee","The ravaging of time thou seest in me"],["Is but the seemly raiment of my heart,","