,"Their mockery of virtue is misled"],["For at a frown they in their glory die.","Their feigned virtue is but treachery"],["The painful warrior famoused for fight,","Your visage and your posture, stern and tight,"],["After a thousand victories once foil'd,","Like serpent set for battle, tense and coiled,"],["Is from the book of honour razed quite,","Ready to strike provok'd, being checked in might"],["And all the rest forgot for which he toil'd:","But never seeing reputation soiled"],["Then happy I, that love and am beloved","So long as my pen flows and I am moved"],["Where I may not remove nor be removed.","Find I am by thy presence great improved."]],[["Lord of my love, to whom in vassalage","Blessed finding myself in thy vassalage"],["Thy merit hath my duty strongly knit,","I've found my path in life so clearly lit"],["To thee I send this written embassage,","Upon this earth I have been given passage"],["To witness duty, not to show my wit:","And in thy service I do proudly sit"],["Duty so great, which wit so poor as mine","My poor verse fail describing raiments fine,"],["May make seem bare, in wanting words to show it,","The Sun so fair arrayed and all below it,"],["But that I hope some good conceit of thine","If thy good flows inspired in verses mine,"],["In thy soul's thought, all naked, will bestow it;","I gift them to thee so that thou mayst know it"],["Till whatsoever star that guides my moving","My very soul, deficient yet improving"],["Points on me graciously with fair aspect","It doth on thee imperfectly reflect"],["And puts apparel on my tatter'd loving,","At times the Muse's song through me is moving"],["To show me worthy of thy sweet respect:","And burnishes my honor and respect"],["Then may I dare to boast how I do love thee;","If you are false, wait til I cease to be:"],["Till then not show my head where thou mayst prove me.","If you are true, my heart belongs to thee"]],[["Weary with toil, I haste me to my bed,","With thoughts of you my aching mind is fed,"],["The dear repose for limbs with travel tired;","When I shed clothes and lie in bed, retired,"],["But then begins a journey in my head,","And I in weariness am to dreams led"],["To work my mind, when body's work's expired:","To touch the flesh that I've from far admired"],["For then my thoughts, from far where I abide,","When sun's last rays in western skies have died"],["Intend a zealous pilgrimage to thee,","As I seek solace where I've oft retired"],["And keep my drooping eyelids open wide,","Imagining thee warm here by my side"],["Looking on darkness which the blind do see","Awake far past the hour I'd have expired"],["Save that my soul's imaginary sight","The moon, so pale and silent in its flight,"],["Presents thy shadow to my sightless view,","Doth dip below window sill, out of view;"],["Which, like a jewel hung in ghastly night,","Its pale glow still illuminates the night"],["Makes black night beauteous and her old face new.","Reflects pale moonlight into gorgeous hue"],["Lo! thus, by day my limbs, by night my mind,","Though seek I solace, ahead and then behind,"],["For thee and for myself no quiet find.","I close my eyes but dark strikes me not blind."]],[["How can I then return in happy plight,","When I do toss and turn in mournful night"],["That am debarr'd the benefit of rest?","And suffer all the day, my mood depress'd,"],["When day's oppression is not eased by night,","When mirror shows me lonely by daylight"],["But day by night, and night by day, oppress'd?","And in the night my skin goes uncaress'd"],["And each, though enemies to either's reign,","My aching back and racing, fevered brain"],["Do in consent shake hands to torture me;","Conspire with each other to torture me"],["The one by toil, the other to complain","The void in mmy bed bids my heat to drain"],["How far I toil, still farther off from thee.","Which makes me shiver nightly without thee"],["I tell the day, to please them thou art bright","Thus welcome I the lark in morning flight"],["And dost him grace when clouds do blot the heaven:","And bid the moon shine bright so thou art seen"],["So flatter I the swart-complexion'd night,","The owl may sing thy song by dark of night"],["When sparkling stars twire not thou gild'st the even.","And also praise the day, my praises even."],["But day doth daily draw my sorrows longer","Thy absence makes the day seem dark and longer."],["And night doth nightly make grief's strength seem stronger.","By night it only makes my passions stronger."]],[["When, in disgrace with fortune and men's eyes,","When in disgrace of Fortune and men's eyes"],["I all alone beweep my outcast state","Pathetically I curse my outcast state"],["And trouble deaf heaven with my bootless cries","And all alone my wretched state despise"],["And look upon myself and curse my fate,","And fall to earth and rue my mournful fate"],["Wishing me like to one more rich in hope,","I feel then like one starved of love and hope,"],["Featured like him, like him with friends possess'd,","One feeling quite like chastened, beaten beast;"],["Desiring this man's art and that man's scope,","Yet seeing noose when contemplating rope"],["With what I most enjoy contented least;","And feeling famine at another's feast"],["Yet in these thoughts myself almost despising,","I find myself my wretched life despising"],["Haply I think on thee, and then my state,","And cursing bitterly my lonely fate"],["Like to the lark at break of day arising","As like the raven, from the ground arising,"],["From sullen earth, sings hymns at heaven's gate;","That scolds and preens while perching on my gate."],["For thy sweet love remember'd such wealth brings","When I think on thee though my heart so sings"],["That then I scorn to change my state with kings.","That I'd not switch place with the greatest kings"]],[["When to the sessions of sweet silent thought","When to the weakened power of my dim thought"],["I summon up remembrance of things past,","I seek some solace in a brighter past"],["I sigh the lack of many a thing I sought,","I find myself in easy comforts caught:"],["And with old woes new wail my dear time's waste:","Nostalgia's limpid pool finds my line cast"],["Then can I drown an eye, unused to flow,","The times I'm trapped besieged by hated foe;"],["For precious friends hid in death's dateless night,","And struggle hard just to survive the night"],["And weep afresh love's long since cancell'd woe,","I force myself in darkness still to go"],["And moan the expense of many a vanish'd sight:","And struggle to remember sweet delight."],["Then can I grieve at grievances foregone,","I'll curse my fate that day when you're gone"],["And heavily from woe to woe tell o'er","And pine for comforts locked behind heaven's door"],["The sad account of fore-bemoaned moan,","I'll rue the sting of every loveless dawn"],["Which I new pay as if not paid before.","And hate that I will suffer many more."],["But if the while I think on thee, dear friend,","A blessing and a curse is my dear friend:"],["All losses are restored and sorrows end.","I treasure thee but I do fear thy end."]],[["Thy bosom is endeared with all hearts,","There is an innocence in untried hearts"],["Which I by lacking have supposed dead,","Which in their innocence no woes have fed;"],["And there reigns love and all love's loving parts,","My inspiration comes in fits and starts"],["And all those friends which I thought buried.","Which have in me, despairing, long since fled;"],["How many a holy and obsequious tear","Your cynical, deceptive crafted tear"],["Hath dear religious love stol'n from mine eye","Deceives us in false o'er-brimming eye;"],["As interest of the dead, which now appear","You've shown me virtues that I hold most dear"],["But things removed that hidden in thee lie!","And yet in beauty's face I give a sigh;"],["Thou art the grave where buried love doth live,","In my sparse-decorated room then I still live"],["Hung with the trophies of my lovers gone,","By winter's chill now cut through to the bone"],["Who all their parts of me to thee did give;","To only thee I now my heart do give"],["That due of many now is thine alone:","Now that in nakedness my shame is shown"],["Their images I loved I view in thee,","My flaws and failures are all plain to see"],["And thou, all they, hast all the all of me.","I show myself plain, hidden not from thee"]],[["If thou survive my well-contented day,","While thou dost live and in the grass still play"],["When that churl Death my bones with dust shall cover,","And mold not in the grave but graze in clover"],["And shalt by fortune once more re-survey","And in my absence deignest to assay"],["These poor rude lines of thy deceased lover,","These modest lines of your poor absent lover;"],["Compare them with the bettering of the time,","Conspires to fade them with accomplice Time,"],["And though they be outstripp'd by every pen,","Regard you then these lines, however thin;"],["Reserve them for my love, not for their rhyme,","I hope you treasure this, my heartfelt rhyme,"],["Exceeded by the height of happier men.","So as you read the rhymes of other men"],["O, then vouchsafe me but this loving thought:","I hope you'll say e'en as I start to rot:"],["'Had my friend's Muse grown with this growing age,","'This poet loves me far beyond his age:"],["A dearer birth than this his love had brought,","But for his dotage it would be his lot"],["To march in ranks of better equipage:","To print my virtues upon virgin page"],["But since he died and poets better prove,","Though other poets' lines rank far above,"],["Theirs for their style I'll read, his for his love.'","Each line of his was written with true love.'"]],[["Full many a glorious morning have I seen","Ablaze in daylight, proudly felt and seen,"],["Flatter the mountain-tops with sovereign eye,","The glorious sun his majesty decree"],["Kissing with golden face the meadows green,","From dawn to dusk and moments in-between"],["Gilding pale streams with heavenly alchemy;","But then he'll slip away, for none to see,"],["Anon permit the basest clouds to ride","Behind a dreary mournful grey cloud slide"],["With ugly rack on his celestial face,","A gauzy film obscuring his fair face"],["And from the forlorn world his visage hide,","Coy and shy, scurrying now to hide,"],["Stealing unseen to west with this disgrace:","His beauty vanishing without a trace."],["Even so my sun one early morn did shine","The sun emerges briefly then to shine"],["With all triumphant splendor on my brow;","And to the world a fleeting warmth endow"],["But out, alack! he was but one hour mine;","Though he once did blaze forth in raiments fine"],["The region cloud hath mask'd him from me now.","A dim shadow of himself shows he now."],["Yet him for this my love no whit disdaineth;","My friends love shines through even when it raineth;"],["Suns of the world may stain when heaven's sun staineth.","Sunlit or not, his care for me remaineth."]],[["Why didst thou promise such a beauteous day,","Oh fickle sun, you heat me ere storm's way"],["And make me travel forth without my cloak,","And sweat me into taking off my cloak"],["To let base clouds o'ertake me in my way,","I misplace my warm coat by heat of day"],["Hiding thy bravery in their rotten smoke?","And in my folly 'gainst the cold winds choke"],["'Tis not enough that through the cloud thou break,","Your rays, though absent soon, do broil and bake"],["To dry the rain on my storm-beaten face,","To slow my courser to a sluggish pace,"],["For no man well of such a salve can speak","Thou wouldst me urge a weak palliative to take"],["That heals the wound and cures not the disgrace:","Instead of heal my disease and disgrace"],["Nor can thy shame give physic to my grief;","You heretic, you question my belief"],["Though thou repent, yet I have still the loss:","You rob me, then call careless my grave loss,"],["The offender's sorrow lends but weak relief","You mock me and compare me in my grief"],["To him that bears the strong offence's cross.","To one who sits and idly gathers moss"],["Ah! but those tears are pearl which thy love sheds,","But then my eyes catch thine and quench my needs,"],["And they are rich and ransom all ill deeds.","Til then the lack of you my passion feeds."]],[["No more be grieved at that which thou hast done:","Some beauty thrives in darkness; yours is one:"],["Roses have thorns, and silver fountains mud;","As even silver fountains do hide mud,"],["Clouds and eclipses stain both moon and sun,","Foul deeds are oft concealed, in darkness done,"],["And loathsome canker lives in sweetest bud.","Madness is hid in brain, sickness in blood;"],["All men make faults, and even I in this,","I find myself, confronted by thy kiss,"],["Authorizing thy trespass with compare,","A smile alone from thee would lay me bare"],["Myself corrupting, salving thy amiss,","When blinded am I by my love and bliss"],["Excusing thy sins more than thy sins are;","I find myself to stumble and to err."],["For to thy sensual fault I bring in sense--","Thus summoned to court I do find me hence:"],["Thy adverse party is thy advocate--","Resigning myself to my guilty fate,"],["And 'gainst myself a lawful plea commence:","I prosecute myself and give a weak defense"],["Such civil war is in my love and hate","A mere kiss from thee would desires sate."],["That I an accessary needs must be","Thy fickleness I compare bitterly"],["To that sweet thief which sourly robs from me.","To winds that blow forth sudden on the sea."]],[["Let me confess that we two must be twain,","The world wills that we two should be split twain"],["Although our undivided loves are one:","Though in a single spirit we stay one;"],["So shall those blots that do with me remain","I bleed with loss of thee and feel the pain"],["Without thy help by me be borne alone.","Long after from my presence thou art gone"],["In our two loves there is but one respect,","Thy absence from me sharpens my respect"],["Though in our lives a separable spite,","And drags long hours from my sleepless night"],["Which though it alter not love's sole effect,","It hones my pen as I miss your aspect,"],["Yet doth it steal sweet hours from love's delight.","When I should sleep I'm at my desk upright"],["I may not evermore acknowledge thee,","I beg thee not to sing my misery"],["Lest my bewailed guilt should do thee shame,","Nor praise my lesser verses, to my shame,"],["Nor thou with public kindness honour me,","But trust thee to keep me in memory"],["Unless thou take that honour from thy name:","I only ask my verses bear my name."],["But do not so; I love thee in such sort","Our memories will each other long support"],["As, thou being mine, mine is thy good report.","E'en if our time upon this earth is short"]],[["As a decrepit father takes delight","As feels a feeble panther stripped of might"],["To see his active child do deeds of youth,","So sapped of strength and dulled of claw and tooth,"],["So I, made lame by fortune's dearest spite,","This poet, with his weakened, blunted bite,"],["Take all my comfort of thy worth and truth.","Doth struggle to describe thy grace and truth."],["For whether beauty, birth, or wealth, or wit,","I strike then to enlighten, candle lit,"],["Or any of these all, or all, or more,","And feeling less a poet than a boor,"],["Entitled in thy parts do crowned sit,","Though 'gainst thy beauty I feel quite unfit"],["I make my love engrafted to this store:","But my weak wine still in fine goblets pour"],["So then I am not lame, poor, nor despised,","My days now grow more short so be advised"],["Whilst that this shadow doth such substance give","Long as I have to thee words left to give"],["That I in thy abundance am sufficed","Read these immortal lines I have devised"],["And by a part of all thy glory live.","And joy in thee increased while I still live"],["Look, what is best, that best I wish in thee:","Long as my words inked black are, all in thee"],["This wish I have; then ten times happy me!","Surviveth in my verse for all to see."]],[["How can my Muse want subject to invent,","Sometimes it seems that thou art heaven sent"],["While thou dost breathe, that pour'st into my verse","A mortal muse brought forth to spur great verse"],["Thine own sweet argument, too excellent","Though others falsely praise thee, art thou meant"],["For every vulgar paper to rehearse?","To buy false praises with a corrupt purse?"],["O, give thyself the thanks, if aught in me","The inspiration that you spark in me"],["Worthy perusal stand against thy sight;","Should feel my dim flame amplified so bright"],["For who's so dumb that cannot write to thee,","'Tis trivial to aptly describe thee:"],["When thou thyself dost give invention light?","Put out a candle--thou describest night!"],["Be thou the tenth Muse, ten times more in worth","Be thus crown'd as a tenth muse on this earth,"],["Than those old nine which rhymers invocate;","And I would be thy devoted oblate"],["And he that calls on thee, let him bring forth","All poetry paid tribute on thy birth,"],["Eternal numbers to outlive long date.","Oblations rich upon Olympus' gate."],["If my slight Muse do please these curious days,","I bear thy burden now and all my days:"],["The pain be mine, but thine shall be the praise.","Each star be poet that lights thee with its rays"]],[["O, how thy worth with manners may I sing,","The best in thee I do attempt to sing,"],["When thou art all the better part of me?","For singing of thee shows the best in me;"],["What can mine own praise to mine own self bring?","My virtues show only when I let thine ring"],["And what is 't but mine own when I praise thee?","The best in me can shine only through thee"],["Even for this let us divided live,","I would that we could in each other live"],["And our dear love lose name of single one,","But in absentia claim thee my heart's throne"],["That by this separation I may give","My soul then as thy fiefdom would I give"],["That due to thee which thou deservest alone.","To rule my heart e'en when I am alone"],["O absence, what a torment wouldst thou prove,","My pen against my paper would I prove"],["Were it not thy sour leisure gave sweet leave","And ere my work is done I will not leave"],["To entertain the time with thoughts of love,","I should not lack for time with my sweet love"],["Which time and thoughts so sweetly doth deceive,","And fearing thoughts of when I may bereave."],["And that thou teachest how to make one twain,","This paradox which eases my poor brain:"],["By praising him here who doth hence remain!","From two subtract one, still two shall remain"]],[["Take all my loves, my love, yea, take them all;","Take everything, my love, my whole, my all:"],["What hast thou then more than thou hadst before?","Take everything and strip me to the core"],["No love, my love, that thou mayst true love call;","Take all my lovse, my love, I'm in thy thrall"],["All mine was thine before thou hadst this more.","Take all my love til you can take no more"],["Then if for my love thou my love receivest,","I hope my praise thou honestly receivest"],["I cannot blame thee for my love thou usest;","And not for cruel sport with me amusest,"],["But yet be blamed, if thou thyself deceivest","Enchanting eye whilst thou my heart deceivest,"],["By wilful taste of what thyself refusest.","And in thy cruelty thou thy friend abusest;"],["I do forgive thy robbery, gentle thief,","If thou hast done me wrong beyond belief"],["Although thou steal thee all my poverty;","Thou hast redeemed it in my ecstasy"],["And yet, love knows, it is a greater grief","I've vowed not, from fatigue nor bitter grief,"],["To bear love's wrong than hate's known injury.","To shrink from action, fearing misery"],["Lascivious grace, in whom all ill well shows,","If thou hast thorns, still be to me a rose:"],["Kill me with spites; yet we must not be foes.","Forewarned am I, they do few dangers pose."]],[["Those petty wrongs that liberty commits,","A hungry vulture squats on me and sits"],["When I am sometime absent from thy heart,","And waits to feed upon my dying heart;"],["Thy beauty and thy years full well befits,","Regret thee, but my mistress them admits,"],["For still temptation follows where thou art.","As she ignores my effort and my art"],["Gentle thou art and therefore to be won,","Those who pursue her, her respect unwon,"],["Beauteous thou art, therefore to be assailed;","By so many unworthy still assailed"],["And when a woman woos, what woman's son","Could be false suitors, unfit every one"],["Will sourly leave her till she have prevailed?","Their lusts and efforts shunned and unprevailed"],["Ay me! but yet thou mightest my seat forbear,","If thou wouldst shun me for my verse too bare"],["And chide try beauty and thy straying youth,","In favor of your flatterers most uncouth"],["Who lead thee in their riot even there","You'll face a situation most unfair"],["Where thou art forced to break a twofold truth,","As we confront a barren twofold truth:"],["Hers by thy beauty tempting her to thee,","Mine, by my faults being plain to see;"],["Thine, by thy beauty being false to me.","Thine, by what thou art, and art claimed to be."]],[["That thou hast her, it is not all my grief,","My lady and the one who does me grief"],["And yet it may be said I loved her dearly;","We three do form a sordid misery:"],["That she hath thee, is of my wailing chief,","In thy remorse I should take no relief,"],["A loss in love that touches me more nearly.","There is no balm to sooth this jealousy."],["Loving offenders, thus I will excuse ye:","I cannot claim that you do foul abuse me"],["Thou dost love her, because thou knowst I love her;","No shame in easing passion with a lover"],["And for my sake even so doth she abuse me,","Thy disgrace doth provoke me and amuse me"],["Suffering my friend for my sake to approve her.","I blush for shame, but from this shame seek cover"],["If I lose thee, my loss is my love's gain,","'Tis marvel this twin wound sees me not slain"],["And losing her, my friend hath found that loss;","And in that gain I still bear double loss"],["Both find each other, and I lose both twain,","But losing both would be unbearable pain"],["And both for my sake lay on me this cross:","And would a scar upon my soul emboss"],["But here's the joy; my friend and I are one;","Her promises stir me and make me moan;"],["Sweet flattery! then she loves but me alone.","But with me, she, and thee I'm still alone."]],[["When most I wink, then do mine eyes best see,","I close my eyes each night and cease to see"],["For all the day they view things unrespected;","While life most vivid is in mind reflected"],["But when I sleep, in dreams they look on thee,","In sleep I have no shield to protect me:"],["And darkly bright are bright in dark directed.","Eyes shut, defenses down, no blows deflected"],["Then thou, whose shadow shadows doth make bright,","My Love, who stands pale, gleaming in the night,"],["How would thy shadow's form form happy show","Whose noble soul could not taint hell below"],["To the clear day with thy much clearer light,","Turn even darkness into sweet delight"],["When to unseeing eyes thy shade shines so!","And offer depths too rich to fully know"],["How would, I say, mine eyes be blessed made","I love thee so, I fear I'd be unmade"],["By looking on thee in the living day,","Were I to live while you in grave should lay"],["When in dead night thy fair imperfect shade","The thought that thy fair light will never fade"],["Through heavy sleep on sightless eyes doth stay!","Doth make the darkest darkness bright and gay"],["All days are nights to see till I see thee,","My day's so bright that I can scarcely see"],["And nights bright days when dreams do show thee me.","And still in darkness shines thy form to me."]],[["If the dull substance of my flesh were thought,","If I could soar to thee as fast as thought"],["Injurious distance should not stop my way;","And more than just mind's eye could fly away"],["For then despite of space I would be brought,","Thy soul by my soul would be swiftly sought"],["From limits far remote where thou dost stay.","And I'd not lack thy company any day"],["No matter then although my foot did stand","I'm not alone even on foreign sand"],["Upon the farthest earth removed from thee;","With salty waters cleaving thee from me"],["For nimble thought can jump both sea and land","I wish I'd be near thee upon demand,"],["As soon as think the place where he would be.","If thoughts alone could bring thee close to me"],["But ah! thought kills me that I am not thought,","I'd shed my flesh and gladly be but thought;"],["To leap large lengths of miles when thou art gone,","Could I be thought all carnal sins I'd shun,"],["But that so much of earth and water wrought","So trapped by flesh away from thee I'm caught"],["I must attend time's leisure with my moan,","Deprived of thee I find myself undone."],["Receiving nought by elements so slow","So long as Fate deems from thee I must go"],["But heavy tears, badges of either's woe.","I must reach in my heart our love to know."]],[["The other two, slight air and purging fire,","Twin spirits perch my shoulders and conspire,"],["Are both with thee, wherever I abide;","Nourish and feed each other, side by side,"],["The first my thought, the other my desire,","Opposing each the other, ice and fire,"],["These present-absent with swift motion slide.","They bicker, then they both my actions chide;"],["For when these quicker elements are gone","The one would scold that thou art still unwon"],["In tender embassy of love to thee,","The other calls this hopeless and would see"],["My life, being made of four, with two alone","My soul on high, through this absence undone,"],["Sinks down to death, oppress'd with melancholy;","Doth thirst for word of what has come to be"],["Until life's composition be recured","As missive sent from envoy borne by bird,"],["By those swift messengers return'd from thee,","I am piecemeal fed news from far of thee"],["Who even but now come back again, assured","With news from fields abroad that they have heard"],["Of thy fair health, recounting it to me:","And tales of what I miss and lack bring me"],["This told, I joy; but then no longer glad,","They quarrel and I can't tell good from bad;"],["I send them back again and straight grow sad.","I dwell on what I lost and what I had."]],[["Mine eye and heart are at a mortal war","Two spirits in me for thy love do war,"],["How to divide the conquest of thy sight;","Both jealously do quarrel at thy sight;"],["Mine eye my heart thy picture's sight would bar,","My eye my heart's clear vision would then bar,"],["My heart mine eye the freedom of that right.","Mine heart my eye thy memory would blight."],["My heart doth plead that thou in him dost lie--","My heart demands inside me thou shouldst lie,"],["A closet never pierced with crystal eyes--","Thy beauty it both credits and denies"],["But the defendant doth that plea deny","My eye insists thy beauty none deny"],["And says in him thy fair appearance lies.","And takes leave of my heart and heaves and sighs"],["To 'cide this title is impanneled","Their natures and their wants are intertwined,"],["A quest of thoughts, all tenants to the heart,","A jury of sharp eye and softened heart"],["And by their verdict is determined","Eternal foes to this fate they're consigned;"],["The clear eye's moiety and the dear heart's part:","Twined shall they be, never to grow apart:"],["As thus; mine eye's due is thy outward part,","My eye makes feast upon your outer part"],["And my heart's right thy inward love of heart.","By deeper virtues sated is my heart."]],[["Betwixt mine eye and heart a league is took,","When I repay thy kindness in my book,"],["And each doth good turns now unto the other:","Seek not insincere lines from any other;"],["When that mine eye is famish'd for a look,","When lean eye starves for sights on which to look"],["Or heart in love with sighs himself doth smother,","I turn not to be indulged by another"],["With my love's picture then my eye doth feast","I choose one or the other to be blest:"],["And to the painted banquet bids my heart;","Indulging in its time my aching heart,"],["Another time mine eye is my heart's guest","When eye is closed and taking a short rest,"],["And in his thoughts of love doth share a part:","In sleep it doth not cease to play its part"],["So, either by thy picture or my love,","In absence I cannot escape my love,"],["Thyself away art resent still with me;","Regardless of my base instinct to flee"],["For thou not farther than my thoughts canst move,","Thy vision haunts in dreams sent from above"],["And I am still with them and they with thee;","Even when my eyes are closed I can see thee"],["Or, if they sleep, thy picture in my sight","My heart thus holds thee nightly and daylight"],["Awakes my heart to heart's and eye's delight.","Reveals thee to the eye to my delight"]],[["How careful was I, when I took my way,","Like miser who his treasures doth assay"],["Each trifle under truest bars to thrust,","And bears no will to share them or show trust,"],["That to my use it might unused stay","Each shiny bauble in a vault did lay"],["From hands of falsehood, in sure wards of trust!","Locked safely away from envious eyes and lust"],["But thou, to whom my jewels trifles are,","I would my beauties safe from others bar,"],["Most worthy of comfort, now my greatest grief,","To whom my rarest balms give slight relief"],["Thou, best of dearest and mine only care,","But thou, who art more valuable by far,"],["Art left the prey of every vulgar thief.","Dost cause me with thy absence so much grief"],["Thee have I not lock'd up in any chest,","Like miser storing jewels in tight-locked chest"],["Save where thou art not, though I feel thou art,","Thus shielding eyes away from glorious art"],["Within the gentle closure of my breast,","I stash my love of thee within my breast,"],["From whence at 