 pow'r to sooth."]],[["Not marble, nor the gilded monuments","I pledge that you for many ages hence"],["Of princes, shall outlive this powerful rhyme;","Shall exceed preservation in my rhyme"],["But you shall shine more bright in these contents","This praise of thee in my verse represents"],["Than unswept stone besmear'd with sluttish time.","A victory over chaos and of time;"],["When wasteful war shall statues overturn,","As time and strife do statues overturn"],["And broils root out the work of masonry,","And rot conspires to blot and dim their story"],["Nor Mars his sword nor war's quick fire shall burn","And careless fires spread to singe and burn"],["The living record of your memory.","Erasing monuments to man's glory"],["'Gainst death and all-oblivious enmity","Despair not for the false austerity"],["Shall you pace forth; your praise shall still find room","That now pervades this never-ending gloom"],["Even in the eyes of all posterity","The wasted fruits of thy prosperity"],["That wear this world out to the ending doom.","Shall not be all that greets thee in thy tomb"],["So, till the judgment that yourself arise,","Do not despair though all around you dies;"],["You live in this, and dwell in lover's eyes.","That dies not which goes forth and multiplies."]],[["Sweet love, renew thy force; be it not said","Within thy presence my love would not fade;"],["Thy edge should blunter be than appetite,","That absence saps its fervor and its might"],["Which but to-day by feeding is allay'd,","Whetted by thee is my dull weak blade"],["To-morrow sharpen'd in his former might:","Which gives it edge and makes it sharp and bright"],["So, love, be thou; although to-day thou fill","The briefest sight of thee should make me thrill"],["Thy hungry eyes even till they wink with fullness,","Though leave me wanting even in my fullness"],["To-morrow see again, and do not kill","The idle hours drag and fail to fill"],["The spirit of love with a perpetual dullness.","And starved my spirit is by their sheer dullness"],["Let this sad interim like the ocean be","The ocean too shall pause for you and me"],["Which parts the shore, where two contracted new","Until we reunite and vows renew"],["Come daily to the banks, that, when they see","In faithfulness declared to sweetly see"],["Return of love, more blest may be the view;","A seascape, brief becalmed, in sailor's view;"],["Else call it winter, which being full of care","The dull of spring and autumn and winter bare"],["Makes summer's welcome thrice more wish'd, more rare.","Doth only whet the tongue for summer's fare"]],[["Being your slave, what should I do but tend","Wouldst thou reject me, when I freely bend"],["Upon the hours and times of your desire?","My will to please the one I so admire"],["I have no precious time at all to spend,","Unbidden, I shall idle hours spend,"],["Nor services to do, till you require.","And find myself spurred still by thy fierce fire"],["Nor dare I chide the world-without-end hour","I cherish all my time under your power"],["Whilst I, my sovereign, watch the clock for you,","And willingly do all you bid me to"],["Nor think the bitterness of absence sour","My time is yours to dictate, hour by hour;"],["When you have bid your servant once adieu;","Nor dare presume my thoughts alone speak true"],["Nor dare I question with my jealous thought","It should not then by anyone be thought"],["Where you may be, or your affairs suppose,","That I could any time this treasure lose"],["But, like a sad slave, stay and think of nought","I ponder not the woes of pleasures sought,"],["Save, where you are how happy you make those.","But how to dodge the thorns of your cruel rose."],["So true a fool is love that in your will,","I must declare how faithful is your Will"],["Though you do any thing, he thinks no ill.","And fear that you'll reject me ever still"]],[["That god forbid that made me first your slave,","Were I your consort, nay, your willing slave"],["I should in thought control