l readers should these heed and mourn the same"],["Whether we are mended, or whether better they,","When thou art in the soil and do decay"],["Or whether revolution be the same.","All words should knit a monument to thy name;"],["O, sure I am, the wits of former days","A mediocre muse can great verse raise:"],["To subjects worse have given admiring praise.","With thou to act as target for their praise."]],[["Like as the waves make towards the pebbled shore,","As wave doth follow wave upon the shore"],["So do our minutes hasten to their end;","Which old sand with the new doth grind and blend"],["Each changing place with that which goes before,","The sands seem not depleted from this store"],["In sequent toil all forwards do contend.","And sand and wave meet, never at an end"],["Nativity, once in the main of light,","The moon beshadowed by increasing night"],["Crawls to maturity, wherewith being crown'd,","Cast in earth's shadow and ill-lit by sun,"],["Crooked elipses 'gainst his glory fight,","Doth wane then wax again, reborn in flight,"],["And Time that gave doth now his gift confound.","While Time still blazes like uncaring Sun"],["Time doth transfix the flourish set on youth","And proves Himself both fickle and uncouth"],["And delves the parallels in beauty's brow,","He snatches back what Nature did endow"],["Feeds on the rarities of nature's truth,","Time reaps the old and withers will and youth"],["And nothing stands but for his scythe to mow:","Into extinction when one doth allow"],["And yet to times in hope my verse shall stand,","I urge, renew thyself as ocean's sand;"],["Praising thy worth, despite his cruel hand.","I sing thy praise, and thy faults reprimand."]],[["Is it thy will thy image should keep open","When dreams don't come, I'm in my chamber moping:"],["My heavy eyelids to the weary night?","Dost thou disrupt my sleep with all thy might?"],["Dost thou desire my slumbers should be broken,","Through sleep and drink, not words, I should be coping,"],["