tality"],["'Tis thee, myself, that for myself I praise,","I strive to voice thy song and sing thee praise"],["Painting my age with beauty of thy days.","And to the heavens my thin voice I raise."]],[["Against my love shall be, as I am now,","When we do meekly to Time's cruel scythe bow"],["With Time's injurious hand crush'd and o'er-worn;","As we are to old age unkindly borne,"],["When hours have drain'd his blood and fill'd his brow","Plagued with all the woes Time doth endow"],["With lines and wrinkles; when his youthful morn","Before from this brief life we're cruelly torn"],["Hath travell'd on to age's steepy night,","When twilight's broken and so fades the light"],["And all those beauties whereof now he's king","And the last vestiges of youth that cling"],["Are vanishing or vanish'd out of sight,","Succumb to this incessant siege of blight"],["Stealing away the treasure of his spring;","I rise and meekly do thy praises sing;"],["For such a time do I now fortify","I bow myself, a sacrifice to be,"],["Against confounding age's cruel knife,","And place myself twixt he and Time's cruel scythe"],["That he shall never cut from memory","Long after living saint may cease to be"],["My sweet love's beauty, though my lover's life:","I'll pilgrim to his church and pay his tithe"],["His beauty shall in these black lines be seen,","I'd have my words read after he's not seen"],["And they shall live, and he in them still green.","And with this verse no man shall think him mean."]],[["When I have seen by Time's fell hand defaced","When upon tombs of emperors I've gazed"],["The rich proud cost of outworn buried age;","And set their records down upon my page"],["When sometime lofty towers I see down-razed","Stone monuments and mighty cities razed"],["And brass eternal slave to mortal rage;","The fate of all the world this doth presage"],["When I have seen the hungry ocean gain","When I've returned from sea and seek to gain"],["Advantage on the kingdom of the shore,","My footing on this treacherous sandy shore"],["And the firm soil win of the watery main,","Seen tides recede and then return again"],["Increasing store with loss and loss with store;","And leaving on sand new plain sand still more"],["When I have seen such interchange of state,","'Tis time to harvest, do not hesitate,"],["Or state itself confounded to decay;","November reaping crops that bloomed in May"],["Ruin hath taught me thus to ruminate,","From Nature's law we cannot deviate:"],["That Time will come and take my love away.","All that one borrows one must soon repay."],["This thought is as a death, which cannot choose","My absence thus I do not freely choose:"],["But weep to have that which it fears to lose.","Each moment spent away from thee I lose."]],[["Since brass, nor stone, nor earth, nor boundless sea,","We indulge hopes of immortality,"],["But sad mortality o'er-sways their power,","Survive the march of Time with his slow power"],["How with this rage shall beauty hold a plea,","All riches in this life be gained, then flee,"],["Whose action is no stronger than a flower?","That shall be promised and broke in an hour"],["O, how shall summer's honey breath hold out","O futile war 'gainst Fate, we'll not hold out"],["Against the wreckful siege of battering days,","How is it we could shield our brief, rare days"],["When rocks impregnable are not so stout,","When Time, relentless, chips at all about?"],["Nor gates of steel so strong, but Time decays?","The sea erodes, sun doth bleach as it blaze;"],["O fearful meditation! where, alack,","Shall finest wines be hidden behind sack?"],["Shall Time's best jewel from Time's chest lie hid?","Shall thy time cease with slam of coffin's lid?"],["Or what strong hand can hold his swift foot back?","Shall we define our lives by what they lack?"],["Or who his spoil of beauty can forbid?","By these sad facts my fresh-inked pen is bid;"],["O, none, unless this miracle have might,","My empty page recalls her skin so white"],["That in black ink my love may still shine bright.","And my dark ink her hair, as black as night."]],[["Tired with all these, for restful death I cry,","When I regard the world's cruel treachery"],["As, to behold desert a beggar born,","And behold praises heaped on those I scorn"],["And needy nothing trimm'd in jollity,","And bold truth swapped for mildly pleasing lie"],["And purest faith unhappily forsworn,","And innocence from youth is cruelly torn,"],["And guilded honour shamefully misplaced,","And virtue slow eroded and defaced,"],["And maiden virtue rudely strumpeted,","And arrogance for confidence mislabeled"],["And right perfection wrongfully disgraced,","And acumen with rude cunning replaced"],["And strength by limping sway disabled,","And history true for what is merely fabled"],["And art made tongue-tied by authority,","And timidness mistook for loyalty"],["And folly doctor-like controlling skill,","And weak verse leaves no space on page to fill"],["And simple truth miscall'd simplicity,","And piety false formed from heresy"],["And captive good attending captain ill:","And mighty mountain made by myth from hill"],["Tired with all these, from these would I be gone,","Thou shouldst this regent falsehood cast from throne"],["Save that, to die, I leave my love alone.","And modest good of Truth let reign alone."]],[["Ah! wherefore with infection should he live,","What poet would thy patronage receive"],["And with his presence grace impiety,","With such pretensions toward propriety,"],["That sin by him advantage should achieve","Himself with this false peerage to deceive"],["And lace itself with his society?","To climb the ranks of high society"],["Why should false painting imitate his cheek","Why should he not to be immortal seek"],["And steal dead seeing of his living hue?","So that his light for ages should shine through?"],["Why should poor beauty indirectly seek","Who would, ungrateful, call unfit and weak"],["Roses of shadow, since his rose is true?","These gifts which one should give, willing and true?"],["Why should he live, now Nature bankrupt is,","Doth poet's face pale, sensing things amiss,"],["Beggar'd of blood to blush through lively veins?","Fear in his Muse's passing what remains?"],["For she hath no exchequer now but his,","Thus Nature makes a bank of virtues his,"],["And, proud of many, lives upon his gains.","E'en as thief Time your lifeblood slowly drains"],["O, him she stores, to show what wealth she had","He doth pay forward pleasures to be had"],["In days long since, before these last so bad.","And hoards great stores of worth against the bad."]],[["Thus is his cheek the map of days outworn,","Thy brow, which wrinkles newly do adorn,"],["When beauty lived and died as flowers do now,","Which once was smooth as freshly fallen snow"],["Before the bastard signs of fair were born,","My own hair thins as if by shepherd shorn:"],["Or durst inhabit on a living brow;","Cruel time would strip what nature did endow"],["Before the golden tresses of the dead,","The graves stripped of the ribbons of the dead"],["The right of sepulchres, were shorn away,","Their garments stol'n, their locks then shorn away"],["To live a second life on second head;","My lady's beauty is not by these fed:"],["Ere beauty's dead fleece made another gay:","These ghastly spoils do not my love array."],["In him those holy antique hours are seen,","My love stands proud, all signs of weathering seen"],["Without all ornament, itself and true,","His natural gifts displayed, seasoned but true."],["Making no summer of another's green,","Unpainted birth to death and in-between,"],["Robbing no old to dress his beauty new;","At every point displaying his pure hue;"],["And him as for a map doth Nature store,","I'd have this treasure seen from shore to shore"],["To show false Art what beauty was of yore.","Be seen by ages new forever more"]],[["Those parts of thee that the world's eye doth view","Our time is short, all that you ever knew"],["Want nothing that the thought of hearts can mend;","One day from mortal eyes cruel Death will rend"],["All tongues, the voice of souls, give thee that due,","Long as you live your graces shine quite true"],["Uttering bare truth, even so as foes commend.","And there's no need thy virtues to defend"],["Thy outward thus with outward praise is crown'd;","You lack no power to enchant and astound;"],["But those same tongues that give thee so thine own","Thy inward only in the heart is known"],["In other accents do this praise confound","The foolish are by outward looks beclowned"],["By seeing farther than the eye hath shown.","And fail to see thy graces plainly shown"],["They look into the beauty of thy mind,","When rude and common folk seek thee to bind"],["And that, in guess, they measure by thy deeds;","And bend thee to their base and vulgar needs,"],["Then, churls, their thoughts, although their eyes were kind,","The gardener neglects thy bed, tasteless and blind:"],["To thy fair flower add the rank smell of weeds:","And overrun it is with common weeds"],["But why thy odour matcheth not thy show,","Why art thou choked by vines, however slow?"],["The solve is this, that thou dost common grow.","A question only for Nature to know"]],[["That thou art blamed shall not be thy defect,","Thy dark eyes and pale skin mirror doth reflect:"],["For slander's mark was ever yet the fair;","Those who love not the night won't think thee fair;"],["The ornament of beauty is suspect,","These doubters have no power to deflect"],["A crow that flies in heaven's sweetest air.","Nor for their plain opinions do I care"],["So thou be good, slander doth but approve","The dark rich fertile soil doth suit my love,"],["Thy worth the greater, being woo'd of time;","And also weeds grow well within this clime."],["For canker vice the sweetest buds doth love,","Thou couldst with looks alone all Nature move,"],["And thou present'st a pure unstained prime.","Thou dark and lovely creature, so sublime!"],["Thou hast pass'd by the ambush of young days,","Unworthy so-called peers who their flags raise"],["Either not assail'd or victor being charged;","Claim that to hold thy honor they are charged"],["Yet this thy praise cannot be so thy praise,","'Tis fruitless to brag that they sing thy praise"],["To tie up envy evermore enlarged:","So long as your virtues go unenlarged;"],["If some suspect of ill mask'd not thy show,","If demon children through thy line should flow"],["Then thou alone kingdoms of hearts shouldst owe.","Resentments of your perfections would grow."]],[["No longer mourn for me when I am dead","My spirit will be free when I am dead"],["Then you shall hear the surly sullen bell","And sent to claim reward in Heaven or Hell"],["Give warning to the world that I am fled","With soul flown forth, from anchor'd flesh fresh fled"],["From this vile world, with vilest worms to dwell:","So weep not when they ring my funeral bell"],["Nay, if you read this line, remember not","I love thee in verse, but let not ink blot"],["The hand that writ it; for I love you so","Nor let my page be singed by candle's glow"],["That I in your sweet thoughts would be forgot","But I would rather you think on me not"],["If thinking on me then should make you woe.","Than to mourn me and let your tears flow"],["O, if, I say, you look upon this verse","Allow my corpse to rot but save my verse"],["When I perhaps compounded am with clay,","(At least these sonnets, if not every play...)"],["Do not so much as my poor name rehearse.","And mourn me not if mourning makes days worse"],["But let your love even with my life decay,","But let me be forgotten for that day"],["Lest the wise world should look into your moan","Smile that my verses are so thinly drawn"],["And mock you with me after I am gone.","And know that e'en without me day shall dawn"]],[["O, lest the world should task you to recite","When I succumb at last to cruel Time's bite,"],["What merit lived in me, that you should love","And my last heartbeats fade along with love"],["After my death, dear love, forget me quite,","Why do you stoop therefore my torch to light"],["For you in me can nothing worthy prove;","When you could leave me lit by moon above?"],["Unless you would devise some virtuous lie,","You do indulge me, and I know not why,"],["To do more for me than mine own desert,","You should your loyalties to me convert"],["And hang more praise upon deceased I","Before the hour that I should fail and die"],["Than niggard truth would willingly impart:","When back to dust my body shall revert"],["O, lest your true love may seem false in this,","When we have shared our sad and final kiss"],["That you for love speak well of me untrue,","My last thoughts on this earth shall be of you"],["My name be buried where my body is,","My faults in death I find you do dismiss"],["And live no more to shame nor me nor you.","Though of my virtues dim I beg sing true"],["For I am shamed by that which I bring forth,","I try to waste not time upon this earth,"],["And so should you, to love things nothing worth.","And justify thus my unworthy birth"]],[["That time of year thou mayst in me behold","In days of late when I am frail and old"],["When yellow leaves, or none, or few, do hang","As last leaves of sad autumn still do hang"],["Upon those boughs which shake against the cold,","On branches which grow brittle in the cold"],["Bare ruin'd choirs, where late the sweet birds sang.","And shiver as if bit by Winter's fang."],["In me thou seest the twilight of such day","Vitality is sapped from me each day"],["As after sunset fadeth in the west,","My foliage tinted and abus'd by pest"],["Which by and by black night doth take away,","Cruel Time then then strips the last green leaves of May,"],["Death's second self, that seals up all in rest.","And from me soon the last dry twigs will wrest"],["In me thou see'st the glowing of such fire","When my old bones enflamed are by the pyre"],["That on the ashes of his youth doth lie,","As all who knew me mourn and say goodbye"],["As the death-bed whereon it must expire","My dead flesh then shall burn upon the fire,"],["Consumed with that which it was nourish'd by.","And to the heavens my soul and words will fly"],["This thou perceivest, which makes thy love more strong,","As sun grows short my shadow does grow long"],["To love that well which thou must leave ere long.","And makes more sweet the passing of my song."]],[["But be contented: when that fell arrest","When Death doth topple me and my soul wrest"],["Without all bail shall carry me away,","When my bones in the cold earth do decay,"],["My life hath in this line some interest,","My soul departed, my empty corpse will rest,"],["Which for memorial still with thee shall stay.","Sent down to feed the worms without delay"],["When thou reviewest this, thou dost review","You must know that my heart was always true"],["The very part was consecrate to thee:","I'd never pledge to anyone but thee"],["The earth can have but earth, which is his due;","All that remains of me belongs to you"],["My spirit is thine, the better part of me:","And charged with thee my memory will be"],["So then thou hast but lost the dregs of life,","If prematurely some rogue steals my life,"],["The prey of worms, my body being dead,","If I lay in a dark street, maimed and bled,"],["The coward conquest of a wretch's knife,","I should lie buried, unmourned by any wife,"],["Too base of thee to be remembered.","The body cold and still, the spirit fled."],["The worth of that is that which it contains,","Some record of me then the world retains"],["And that is this, and this with thee remains.","When bones in earth are all that still remains"]],[["So are you to my thoughts as food to life,","As breath from lungs coax pleasant song from fife"],["Or as sweet-season'd showers are to the ground;","My mouth doth water at the joyous sound"],["And for the peace of you I hold such strife","The sight of thee makes hunger spring to life"],["As 'twixt a miser and his wealth is found;","I beg to lick thy plate like hungry hound"],["Now proud as an enjoyer and anon","When day doth break and I do greet the dawn"],["Doubting the filching age will steal his treasure,","I look with discontent on all my treasure"],["Now counting best to be with you alone,","I've found myself belittled, spit upon,"],["Then better'd that the world may see my pleasure;","And at the mercy of another's pleasure;"],["Sometime all full with feasting on your sight","Like miserable cur living by night"],["And by and by clean starved for a look;","By dark emboldened but by daylight shook"],["Possessing or pursuing no delight,","I cower and seek nothing in the light"],["Save what is had or must from you be took.","And morsels from thy plate are meekly took"],["Thus do I pine and surfeit day by day,","I've hungered for thee all the night and day"],["Or gluttoning on all, or all away.","Unsated by that which should make me gay."]],[["Why is my verse so barren of new pride,","How with thy constance thou dost mock the tide,"],["So far from variation or quick change?","Which doth, relentless, all the sands arrange"],["Why with the time do I not glance aside","Why hold I not your hand when by thy side"],["To new-found methods and to compounds strange?","Nor quick shy glimpses with thine eyes exchange?"],["Why write I still all one, ever the same,","I whip my stray impulses 'til they're tame"],["And keep invention in a noted weed,","Thus whipped I write until my hands do bleed"],["That every word doth almost tell my name,","Desire fills me to increase thy fame"],["Showing their birth and where they did proceed?","And thus weak Will is driven by such need"],["O, know, sweet love, I always write of you,","I do not leave my finances askew"],["And you and love are still my argument;","Resenting not to repay what is lent"],["So all my best is dressing old words new,","Borrowing dear to sing of thee anew"],["Spending again what is already spent:","Finding no cause the interest to resent"],["For as the sun is daily new and old,","To speak the obvious sometimes seems bold"],["So is my love still telling what is told.","Summers are warm, winters are sometimes cold."]],[["Thy glass will show thee how thy beauties wear,","A time will come when years make thee less fair,"],["Thy dial how thy precious minutes waste;","When cracks of aging crease across thy face"],["The vacant leaves thy mind's imprint will bear,","Your face the signs of aging soon will bear"],["And of this book this learning mayst thou taste.","This vandalism doth cruel Time disgrace;"],["The wrinkles which thy glass will truly show","Still words on stones, when thou art drawn below,"],["Of mouthed graves will give thee memory;","Till etched name shall fade, this all will see"],["Thou by thy dial's shady stealth mayst know","Act now to save thyself, surely you know"],["Time's thievish progress to eternity.","Relentlessly how time doth suck at thee."],["Look, what thy memory can not contain","Here shall the good of thee be written plain."],["Commit to these waste blanks, and thou shalt find","Within the fertile garden of verse find"],["Those children nursed, deliver'd from thy brain,","My words for those yet unform'd shall remain"],["To take a new acquaintance of thy mind.","For those to see who turn not an eye blind"],["These offices, so oft as thou wilt look,","Your beauty shall shine long as eyes may look,"],["Shall profit thee and much enrich thy book.","Shall stay recorded in a dusty book"]],[["So oft have I invoked thee for my Muse","When I have found and pleased my gentle muse"],["And found such fair assistance in my verse","I beg not meager scraps from thy fat purse"],["As every alien pen hath got my use","My rhymes burst forth once thou has lit their fuse,"],["And under thee their poesy disperse.","Once sparked they are, their course they can't reverse"],["Thine eyes that taught the dumb on high to sing","Thy virtues cause the dullest pipes to sing"],["And heavy ignorance aloft to fly","E'en raven croaks his song in branches high--"],["Have added feathers to the learned's wing","And urge e'en dull chimes fully bright to ring--"],["And given grace a double majesty.","And sing thy praises high into the sky"],["Yet be most proud of that which I compile,","Inspired am I by thy kindly smile,"],["Whose influence is thine and born of thee:","It lures me in as flowers draw the bee"],["In others' works thou dost but mend the style,","Though flattering poems come from rank and file,"],["And arts with thy sweet graces graced be;","In mine alone is true love there to see."],["But thou art all my art and dost advance","More jester than knight, I'll face every lance"],["As high as learning my rude ignorance.","E'en when I, lonely, like a fool still dance"]],[["Whilst I alone did call upon thy aid,","I am not yet to gaze on thee afraid,"],["My verse alone had all thy gentle grace,","If only to inspire me with thy face"],["But now my gracious numbers are decay'd","When time shall come that from this earth I fade"],["And my sick Muse doth give another place.","And all my talents dwindle to a trace"],["I grant, sweet love, thy lovely argument","I'd urge thee thy extinction to prevent;"],["Deserves the travail of a worthier pen,","That with this borrowing thou should grow too thin"],["Yet what of thee thy poet doth invent","Ere Nature's forced to claim these things he's lent"],["He robs thee of and pays it thee again.","He sees they shine not forth in other men;"],["He lends thee virtue and he stole that word","Have pity on this poet, for that apt word"],["From thy behavior; beauty doth he give","That strayed from him when he thy praise did give"],["And found it in thy cheek; he can afford","His duty is, whether heard or unheard,"],["No praise to thee but what in thee doth live.","To shower on you verse while you do live"],["Then thank him not for that which he doth say,","This poet finds thus patience, not dismay,"],["Since what he owes thee thou thyself dost pay.","But still urge thee to wed without delay."]],[["O, how I faint when I of you do write,","My rival's lines lack truth but have more bite;"],["Knowing a better spirit doth use your name,","Mine next to his seem witless, mild and tame."],["And in the praise thereof spends all his might,","He praises thee with lines skillful and light"],["To make me tongue-tied, speaking of your fame!","I do endeavor to repay the same"],["But since your worth, wide as the ocean is,","The symbol of your greatness, as it is,"],["The humble as the proudest sail doth bear,","Shines forth on banners your galleon doth bear."],["My saucy bark inferior far to his","My ill-formed craft may sink or sail amiss"],["On your broad main doth wilfully appear.","Its chances on the ocean still will dare;"],["Your shallowest help will hold me up afloat,","On choppy seas I find myself afloat"],["Whilst he upon your soundless deep doth ride;","My thin white sail dwarfed by tall ships aside"],["Or being wreck'd, I am a worthless boat,","I with a hovel and a sad patched boat,"],["He of tall building and of goodly pride:","Both held together only with my pride."],["Then if he thrive and I be cast away,","I hope that on my passing you will say"],["The worst was this; my love was my decay.","'He truly tried.'  Thus honor me that day."]],[["Or I shall live your epitaph to make,","When thou shalt cease to live and daily wake"],["Or you survive when I in earth am rotten;","And I as well in cold earth do lie rotten"],["From hence your memory death cannot take,","Do not death for obscurity mistake"],["Although in me each part will be forgotten.","For from my verse thou shalt not be forgotten."],["Your name from hence immortal life shall have,","As I approach the end I must be brave."],["Though I, once gone, to all the world must die:","All poets scribe their lines, seek fame, then die."],["The earth can yield me but a common grave,","My destiny is soon a common grave,"],["When you entombed in men's eyes shall lie.","And in this modest dirt my bones will lie"],["Your monument shall be my gentle verse,","I strive to trace thy shadow in my verse"],["Which eyes not yet created shall o'er-read,","And every action of mine fills this need"],["And tongues to be your being shall rehearse","A durable record of your deeds diverse"],["When all the breathers of this world are dead;","Recorded in these books for all to read."],["You still shall live--such virtue hath my pen--","For each dear breath I struggle and breathe out ten,"],["Where breath most breathes, even in the mouths of men.","And when breath fails I still push forth my pen."]],[["I grant thou wert not married to my Muse","This common poet and I have our Muse,"],["And therefore mayst without attaint o'erlook","Though both of us upon her kindly look"],["The dedicated words which writers use","Our verses simple, as one might accuse,"],["Of their fair subject, blessing every book","Would never be for plain true speech mistook"],["Thou art as fair in knowledge as in hue,","My love is great, yet words I find but few,"],["Finding thy worth a limit past my praise,","So in this drought of words I find malaise"],["And therefore art enforced to seek anew","And simple as it should be to speak true,"],["Some fresher stamp of the time-bettering days","I struggle still to sing thee simple praise."],["And do so, love; yet when they have devised","For all the tortured grammar I've devised"],["What strained touches rhetoric can lend,","These wretched rhymes to recall, stitch, and mend,"],["Thou truly fair wert truly sympathized","I find myself now counseled and advised"],["In true plain words by thy true-telling friend;","And struggle yet my last few coins to spend"],["And their gross painting might be better used","Blush not when your few few flaws are thus accused"],["Where cheeks need blood; in thee it is abused.","Thy many virtues never are refused."]],[["I never saw that you did painting need","To falsely paint thy grace there is no need:"],["And therefore to your fair no painting set;","No gilding needs the lily, plainly set,"],["I found, or thought I found, you did exceed","In fertile thoughts of you I plant my seed"],["The barren tender of a poet's debt;","And in my verses true my goals are met"],["And therefore have I slept in your report,","My vivid dreams I suddenly abort"],["That you yourself being extant well might show","And stirring from this slumber I am slow"],["How far a modern quill doth come too short,","I strive thy reputation to support,"],["Speaking of worth, what worth in you doth grow.","Inspir'd above, I brace myself below"],["This silence for my sin you did impute,","To sing of thee and increase thy repute"],["Which shall be most my glory, being dumb;","When others see thy worth yet remain dumb,"],["For I impair not beauty being mute,","When some, demented, would thy worth dispute"],["When others would give life and bring a tomb.","Their thoghts I would discount, worth lowly sum."],["There lives more life in one of your fair eyes","Seek thus to increase--better I'd advise"],["Than both your poets can in praise devise.","So that your beauty evermore shall rise."]],[["Who is it that says most? which can say more","Of all thy virtues, can I say any more,"],["Than this rich praise, that you alone are you?","Than that which in thy visage shineth true?"],["In whose confine immured is the store","All Nature should thee envy to the core,"],["Which should example where your equal grew.","E'en as it did these graces in thee imbue"],["Lean penury within that pen doth dwell","Old praise is like a faded inscribed bell"],["That to his subject lends not some small glory;","Which praiseful words of you once did bear."],["But he that writes of you, if he can tell","The poet's job, with verse to make it knell,"],["That you are you, so dignifies his story,","If his eyes blur, let his vision not blear"],["Let him but copy what in you is writ,","All who use thee as muse should see thee lit"],["Not making worse what nature made so clear,","Though it be more than mortal quill may bear"],["And such a counterpart shall fame his wit,","But finding inspiration that doth fit,"],["Making his style admired every where.","You should accept it and this praise well wear"],["You to your beauteous blessings add a curse,","To their dishonor I do leave this curse:"],["Being fond on praise, which makes your praises worse.","Fare they not well who wish me any worse!"]],[["My tongue-tied Muse in manners holds her still,","My talent to describe you lags my will;"],["While comments of your praise, richly compiled,","While other poets, surer and less wild,"],["Reserve their character with golden quill","With words more fit and clever praise thee still"],["And precious phrase by all the Muses filed.","Yet sing of thee with words too weak and mild."],["I think good thoughts whilst other write good words,","My brain and tongue do tangle thoughts and words"],["And like unletter'd clerk still cry 'Amen'","And struggle hard to make verse flow from pen"],["To every hymn that able spirit affords","And from their flight scribe auguries of birds"],["In polish'd form of well-refined pen.","E'en when its meaning 'scapes my acumen."],["Hearing you praised, I say 'Tis so, 'tis true,'","There are those want of gold makes sing untrue"],["And to the most of praise add something more;","Who'd sing false praises like a common whore"],["But that is in my thought, whose love to you,","My muse, who now draws lines simple but true,"],["Though words come hindmost, holds his rank before.","The last words in me can draw to the fore"],["Then others for the breath of words respect,","I pray the Muse flow through me and correct"],["Me for my dumb thoughts, speaking in effect.","The rhymes that fail to pay thee due respect"]],[["Was it the proud full sail of his great verse,","The urge to write of thee, blessing and curse,"],["Bound for the prize of all too precious you,","Oft imitated yet rivaled by so few"],["That did my ripe thoughts in my brain inhearse,","That drove the block within me to reverse"],["Making their tomb the womb wherein they grew?","And bid me write to keep his best in view"],["Was it his spirit, by spirits taught to write","Was it his wicked wit, its sting and bite"],["Above a mortal pitch, that struck me dead?","Which with its sting my dull ill sloth admonished,"],["No, neither he, nor his compeers by night","That whipped me forth, to versify and write,"],["Giving him aid, my verse astonished.","To urge who knew thee not to be astonished?"],["He, nor that affable familiar ghost","'Tis mortal man, not spirit, wight, or ghost"],["Which nightly gulls him with intelligence","That passes on thy soul for ages hence"],["As victors of my silence cannot boast;","I sit with quill and page thus at my post"],["I was not sick of any fear from thence:","My lines to praise thee fill my pages dense."],["But when your countenance fill'd up his line,","As I observe thy words and virtues fine"],["Then lack'd I matter; that enfeebled mine.","I felt compelled to match this still in mine."]],[["Farewell! thou art too dear for my possessing,","When liberty for thee thou findest ceasing"],["And like enough thou know'st thy estimate:","I watch you slip away beyond my gate."],["The charter of thy worth gives thee releasing;","I hate to find our distance thus increasing"],["My bonds in thee are all determinate.","And losing thee should be my mournful fate."],["For how do I hold thee but by thy granting?","For luxuries to dull this ache I'm hunting"],["And for that riches where is my deserving?","Such trifles are a waste, but we're deserving;"],["The cause of this fair gift in me is wanting,","I imitate not lark nor call of bunting:"],["And so my patent back again is swerving.","My only goal--thy memory preserving."],["Thyself thou gavest, thy own worth then not knowing,","I do despair to see thy foes false-crowing,"],["Or me, to whom thou gavest it, else mistaking;","The worth of thee discounting and mistaking,"],["So thy great gift, upon misprision growing,","I pray that my kind muse, to see rhymes flowing,"],["Comes home again, on better judgment making.","Inspires my dreams until the dawn is breaking"],["Thus have I had thee, as a dream doth flatter,","When morning comes my sheets are in a tatter:"],["In sleep a king, but waking no such matter.","And daybreak's toils my pleasant dreams do scatter"]],[["When thou shalt be disposed to set me light,","When others curse thee I would bring thee light"],["And place my merit in the eye of scorn,","E'en should I find my loyalties cruel torn"],["Upon thy side against myself I'll fight,","Against my own self I would even fight,"],["And prove thee virtuous, though thou art forsworn.","Thy flag by me shall faithfully be borne;"],["With mine own weakness being best acquainted,","With all thy virtues I am well acquainted"],["Upon thy part I can set down a story","Well spent is my time--I'm not sad nor sorry--"],["Of faults conceal'd, wherein I am attainted,","In which I sing thy praise and thou art sainted"],["That thou in losing me shalt win much glory:","And future generations see thy glory."],["And I by this will be a gainer too;","I swear I am thy knight, valorous and true,"],["For bending all my loving thoughts on thee,","I bear thy banner for all foes to see"],["The injuries that to myself I do,","I hope to win a victory with you"],["Doing thee vantage, double-vantage me.","And hope you see a champion in me"],["Such is my love, to thee I so belong,","Thy cross I'd bear, thy comfort to prolong,"],["That for thy right myself will bear all wrong.","I suffer not while I do sing thy song."]],[["Say that thou didst forsake me for some fault,","Deny my eloquence, my spice and salt,"],["And I will comment upon that offence;","Accuse me of poor taste and lack of sense,"],["Speak of my lameness, and I straight will halt,","Claim my weak beer lacks both of hops and malt"],[