in to pass,"],["At first the very worst of fortune's might,","A greater harm that saps them of their might."],["And other strains of woe, which now seem woe,","A wound from you before I am struck low"],["Compared with loss of thee will not seem so.","Will dull the blows of the most fearsome foe."]],[["Some glory in their birth, some in their skill,","Some in their looks and beauty take a thrill,"],["Some in their wealth, some in their bodies' force,","Some in their strength and raw power and force,"],["Some in their garments, though new-fangled ill,","Some in the sport, to seek their prey to kill,"],["Some in their hawks and hounds, some in their horse;","Some pride themselves in mercy and remorse;"],["And every humour hath his adjunct pleasure,","Some in their spending, some in hoarded treasure,"],["Wherein it finds a joy above the rest:","Some in their gentleness, some in stll peace;"],["But these particulars are not my measure;","Some in capacity to suck life's pleasure"],["All these I better in one general best.","No urge to write of them lies in my breast"],["Thy love is better than high birth to me,","When in mind's eye your visage do I see"],["Richer than wealth, prouder than garments' cost,","Above all riches thou art treasured most;"],["Of more delight than hawks or horses be;","I'd not trade immortality for thee,"],["And having thee, of all men's pride I boast:","Nor of immortal love naively boast."],["Wretched in this alone, that thou mayst take","And yet the death of thee would cruelly take"],["All this away and me most wretched make.","And cause a thirst in me no draught could slake"]],[["But do thy worst to steal thyself away,","That we are mortal, fear not nor dismay,"],["For term of life thou art assured mine,","Long on this earth thy fair deeds will still shine"],["And life no longer than thy love will stay,","My verse insures thy legacy shan't decay"],["For it depends upon that love of thine.","So long as I can sing of virtues thine"],["Then need I not to fear the worst of wrongs,","Our time on this cruel earth does not last long:"],["When in the least of them my life hath end.","In joy or void, all suffering must end."],["I see a better state to me belongs","Thy traits and deeds will live on in my song"],["Than that which on thy humour doth depend;","And to thy glory I my words do bend"],["Thou canst not vex me with inconstant mind,","I would my fortune to thy fortune bind"],["Since that my life on thy revolt doth lie.","Our causes just, we should join and ally"],["O, what a happy title do I find,","I could not be to thy good virtues blind;"],["Happy to have thy love, happy to die!","You seem perfection, this I can't deny."],["But what's so blessed-fair that fears no blot?","Upon my thoughts there is one darkened blot:"],["Thou mayst be false, and yet I know it not.","Thou couldst be false and I may know it not."]],[["So shall I live, supposing thou art true,","I must deny what's obviously true,"],["Like a deceived husband; so love's face","To be deprived of sight of thy fair face"],["May still seem love to me, though alter'd new;","Torments me when I find it out of view."],["Thy looks with me, thy heart in other place:","To be without thy love would be disgrace."],["For there can live no hatred in thine eye,","We marvel at mad Love's queer mystery"],["Therefore in that I cannot know thy change.","But we do strive to kindly rearrange"],["In many's looks the false heart's history","The visions we have in its reverie"],["Is writ in moods and frowns and wrinkles strange,","Appears not endless but doth morph and change"],["But heaven in thy creation did decree","Those yet unborn should thy fair visage see"],["That in thy face sweet love should ever dwell;","In paying yourself forward you'd do well;"],["Whate'er thy thoughts or thy heart's workings be,","As long as traces of you there shall be"],["Thy looks should nothing thence but sweetness tell.","Your fair face will thy virtues ever tell"],["How like Eve's apple doth thy beauty grow,","No others in the future will thee know"],["if thy sweet virtue answer not thy show!","When lights in thy bright eyes do cease to glow"]],[["They that have power to hurt and will do none,","Those who collect abuse but return none"],["That do not do the thing they most do show,","Who suffer but through whom no evils flow;"],["Who, moving others, are themselves as stone,","Who quietly stir others to good deeds done"],["Unmoved, cold, and to temptation slow,","Who reap less good than they do generously sow"],["They rightly do inherit heaven's graces","They pay the world then generously with their graces"],["And husband nature's riches from expense;","Each kindness loaned they fairly recompense"],["They are the lords and owners of their faces,","Remembered ever shall be their kind faces"],["Others but stewards of their excellence.","And their good deads will be known in years hence;"],["The summer's flower is to the summer sweet,","The noble rose bursts forth with blossoms sweet"],["Though to itself it only live and die,","And gifts the eye with beauteous symmetry"],["But if that flower with base infection meet,","But often within a canker lies to greet"],["The basest weed outbraves his dignity:","No stench is greater than this treachery"],["For sweetest things turn sourest by their deeds;","No beauty hides the stench of evil deeds"],["Lilies that fester smell far worse than weeds.","And nothing good should grow from withered seeds"]],[["How sweet and lovely dost thou make the shame","A fruit with conceal'd rot may smell the same"],["Which, like a canker in the fragrant rose,","Mere knowledge of how sweet smells canker'd rose"],["Doth spot the beauty of thy budding name!","A poisoned drink doth quench thirst still the same:"],["O, in what sweets dost thou thy sins enclose!","My mistress shines e'en when her faults she shows."],["That tongue that tells the story of thy days,","This cruel cat, with me her mouse, she plays;"],["Making lascivious 