em doth compel"],["Or from their proud lap pluck them where they grew;","And wakens in them inspirations new"],["Nor did I wonder at the lily's white,","I sing not of the moon's pale, stolen light"],["Nor praise the deep vermilion in the rose;","Nor of the rose's scent and garish clothes;"],["They were but sweet, but figures of delight,","They are compared to your sweet, pure delight"],["Drawn after you, you pattern of all those.","Mere trifles to tide over eye and nose."],["Yet seem'd it winter still, and, you away,","Blinded by your grace, I sightless pray,"],["As with your shadow I with these did play:","And even sightless seek thee to repay"]],[["The forward violet thus did I chide:","The thieving rose I did viciously chide"],["Sweet thief, whence didst thou steal thy sweet that smells,","For having copied my love's tints and smells"],["If not from my love's breath? The purple pride","This fail'd crime 'gainst my mistress it doth hide,"],["Which on thy soft cheek for complexion dwells","Holds only the dulled might of echoed bells"],["In my love's veins thou hast too grossly dyed.","The last time I stood trembling by your side"],["The lily I condemned for thy hand,","The rarest blooms I did put in thy hand"],["And buds of marjoram had stol'n thy hair:","Thou didst a moment hold then set aside;"],["The roses fearfully on thorns did stand,","Three thieving roses did I reprimand;"],["One blushing shame, another white despair;","The first two rogues to steal thy hue had tried."],["A third, nor red nor white, had stol'n of both","A third had in his vile crimes had outdone both"],["And to his robbery had annex'd thy breath;","And strove to snatch thy scent but was denied."],["But, for his theft, in pride of all his growth","At this disgrace proud Nature curs'd him, wroth:"],["A vengeful canker eat him up to death.","He rotted then and suffered unmourn'd death."],["More flowers I noted, yet I none could see","He seemed to all a beauty plain to see"],["But sweet or colour it had stol'n from thee.",""]],[["Where art thou, Muse, that thou forget'st so long","Why does thou, Muse, forsake me for so long?"],["To speak of that which gives thee all thy might?","Waste thou thy time on trifles, out of sight?"],["Spend'st thou thy fury on some worthless song,","Wouldst thou withhold thy vigor from my song,"],["Darkening thy power to lend base subjects light?","Why dost thou not step forth into the light?"],["Return, forgetful Muse, and straight redeem","As wasteful hours with poets you may deem"],["In gentle numbers time so idly spent;","Thy time with me I swear is wisely spent"],["Sing to the ear that doth thy lays esteem","Though risky ill investment it may seem,"],["And gives thy pen both skill and argument.","I will repay with interest all that's lent"],["Rise, resty Muse, my love's sweet face survey,","Let slack thy labors, goldbrick and delay,"],["If Time have any wrinkle graven there;","In efforts to despoil him take no care,"],["If any, be a satire to decay,","I beg thee, Nature, speed not his decay"],["And make Time's spoils despised every where.","But leave him forth untouched, aged but fair"],["Give my love fame faster than Time wastes life;","Flow swift my pen to capture him in life"],["So thou prevent'st his scythe and crooked knife.","And hone my love as whetstone sharpens knife"]],[["O truant Muse, what shall be thy amends","What plans hast thou to make thy due amends"],["For thy neglect of truth in beauty dyed?","When pen runs dry and I'm by words defied?"],["Both truth and beauty on my love depends;","A desperate cry for help my poor soul sends"],["So dost thou too, and therein dignified.","Yet by my muse I'm cruelly denied."],["Make answer, Muse: wilt thou not haply say","Why should these delights fade with end of day?"],["'Truth needs no colour, with his colour fix'd;","That beauty should be in this world firm fix'd"],["Beauty no pencil, beauty's truth to lay;","Beauty immortal sheared from mortal stay,"],["But best is best, if never intermix'd?'","Art thou so cruel that you'd not see them mix'd?"],["Because he needs no praise, wilt thou be dumb?","Why, muse, do you stand there before me dumb?"],["Excuse not silence so; for't lies in thee","His beauty shuns admirers, will thou not see?"],["To make him much outlive a gilded tomb,","Think on't, bid his due words to come"],["And to be praised of ages yet to be.","Stand not before me mute, inspire me!"],["Then do thy office, Muse; I teach thee how","In my last Spring, seeds I do plant and plow"],["To make him seem long hence as he shows now.","To feed a harvest that starts long from now."]],[["My love is strengthen'd, though more weak in seeming;","E'en should the distance dull my passion's gleaming"],["I love not less, though less the show appear:","Or starlings light and strip the harvest bare"],["That love is merchandized whose rich esteeming","Should jealous eye observe me at thee beaming,"],["The owner's tongue doth publish every where.","I would not for their scorn give any care"],["Our love was new and then but in the spring","The meadlowlark did let they praises ring"],["When I was wont to greet it with my lays,","The mourning dove doth also greet sun's rays"],["As Philomel in summer's front doth sing","In sparer days in hunger she doth sing"],["And stops her pipe in growth of riper days:","And still her soft coos fill the brightest days"],["Not that the summer is less pleasant now","The quiet twilight sooths me no more now"],["Than when her mournful hymns did hush the night,","This moment when day fadeth into night"],["But that wild music burthens every bough","Crepuscular creatures scurry 'neath each bough"],["And sweets grown common lose their dear delight.","Upon the hour when bat and owl take flight;"],["Therefore like her I sometime hold my tongue,","Yet I stay silent when my words feel wrong"],["Because I would not dull you with my song.","And stay content with nightingale's sad song."]],[["Alack, what poverty my Muse brings forth,","As Death steps forth to reap fruits of my birth"],["That having such a scope to show her pride,","And sweeps the flower of my verse aside;"],["The argument all bare is of more worth","In my rapt silence I do find more worth"],["Than when it hath my added praise beside!","Than all the rhymes my poor wit could provide"],["O, blame me not, if I no more can write!","At twilight hour, when day turns into night,"],["Look in your glass, and there appears a face","When sun doth fade and moonlight lights thy face,"],["That over-goes my blunt invention quite,","Thy raven hair fair framing skin so white."],["Dulling my lines and doing me disgrace.","I find my verse far oustripped by thy grace."],["Were it not sinful then, striving to mend,","When sleepless hours at my desk I spend"],["To mar the subject that before was well?","I find myself back ringing thy fair bell"],["For to no other pass my verses tend","I rifle through past rhymes, and these amend,"],["Than of your graces and your gifts to tell;","And of no other subject can I tell."],["And more, much more, than in my verse can sit","I'd paint thee plain as thou art by Sun lit"],["Your own glass shows you when you look in it.","If only I did not lack the sharp wit!"]],[["To me, fair friend, you never can be old,","Even as you yet unmarried do grow old"],["For as you were when first your eye I eyed,","Unworthy next to you seems any bride,"],["Such seems your beauty still. Three winters cold","Three years with sheets unshared and bed still cold"],["Have from the forests shook three summers' pride,","You've wasted with no woman by your side;"],["Three beauteous springs to yellow autumn turn'd","An austere reputation you have earned"],["In process of the seasons have I seen,","In public with no lover to be seen"],["Three April perfumes in three hot Junes burn'd,","Three winters' worth of summer's saplings burned"],["Since first I saw you fresh, which yet are green.","Once autumn has dried wood that had been green"],["Ah! yet doth beauty, like a dial-hand,","Last rays of sun still warm the cooling land"],["Steal from his figure and no pace perceived;","Fade slowly so its loss is scarce perceived"],["So your sweet hue, which methinks still doth stand,","Thy puissant seed, I do thee reprimand,"],["Hath motion and mine eye may be deceived:","Should not pass by in this world received;"],["For fear of which, hear this, thou age unbred;","I urge you take a bride, it must be said;"],["Ere you were born was beauty's summer dead.","All Nature is a widow with thee dead."]],[["Let not my love be call'd idolatry,","I do not falsely claim virtues in thee,"],["Nor my beloved as an idol show,","Enough already teem in thee and grow"],["Since all alike my songs and praises be","I'd also not claim shares of these in me,"],["To one, of one, still such, and ever so.","Compared to thee I am but dull and slow"],["Kind is my love to-day, to-morrow kind,","I would with words thy virtues to thee bind"],["Still constant in a wondrous excellence;","I do this and ask nought for recompense;"],["Therefore my verse to constancy confined,","The good in thee leaves me to thy faults blind,"],["One thing expressing, leaves out difference.","And robs me of my easily swayed sense"],["'Fair, kind and true' is all my argument,","You bear the jewels of heaven, sparsely sent,"],["'Fair, kind, and true' varying to other words;","Distributed meagerly--Nature hoards;"],["And in this change is my invention spent,","A miser could thee sing with three words spent,"],["Three themes in one, which wondrous scope affords.","And find that he still many more affords"],["'Fair, kind, and true,' have often lived alone,","Most people find themselves arrayed with none"],["Which three till now never kept seat in one.","But in thy character they fuse as one."]],[["When in the chronicle of wasted time","When we look back upon a nobler time"],["I see descriptions of the fairest wights,","Attention turns to thin frivolous flights,"],["And beauty making beautiful old rhyme","Bold prose of noble deeds and florid rhyme"],["In praise of ladies dead and lovely knights,","That sings of maidens fair and gallant knights."],["Then, in the blazon of sweet beauty's best,","In their array thought noblest and best"],["Of hand, of foot, of lip, of eye, of brow,","Their stories do inspire, I'll allow,"],["I see their antique pen would have express'd","But all is vanity.  Time shall arrest"],["Even such a beauty as you master now.","What these romantic notions do endow."],["So all their praises are but prophecies","When sages on earth look'd for prophecies"],["Of this our time, all you prefiguring;","Their hopes from horoscopes a bright path figuring"],["And, for they look'd but with divining eyes,","They deemed their calculations of thee but a tease"],["They had not skill enough your worth to sing:","And longed for the delights you would be triggering."],["For we, which now behold these present days,","Those who were born too far before your days"],["Had eyes to wonder, but lack tongues to praise.","Rue that they passed before they knew thy ways."]],[["Not mine own fears, nor the prophetic soul","No horoscope nor sign in flight of gull"],["Of the wide world dreaming on things to come,","That tells of days past and days yet to come"],["Can yet the lease of my true love control,","Can drive me to describe thee well in full,"],["Supposed as forfeit to a confined doom.","Inspired by your worth but still struck dumb;"],["The mortal moon hath her eclipse endured","When dark days as predicted we've endured"],["And the sad augurs mock their own presage;","As gloomy omens past did ill presage"],["Incertainties now crown themselves assured","Til days are at their end, glory ensured,"],["And peace proclaims olives of endless age.","And we must with Apocalypse engage"],["Now with the drops of this most balmy time","Despite the passing of that cruel thief, time,"],["My love looks fresh, and death to me subscribes,","Which sucks our sap, our lifeblood cruel imbibes"],["Since, spite of him, I'll live in this poor rhyme,","Eventually leaves nothing but my rhyme"],["While he insults o'er dull and speechless tribes:","Which my beloved faithfully describes"],["And thou in this shalt find thy monument,","There comes a time when Death will not relent,"],["When tyrants' crests and tombs of brass are spent.","When life fades and vitality is spent."]],[["What's in the brain that ink may character","When urge in me to write of thee doth stir"],["Which hath not figured to thee my true spirit?","What can be written so the page can bear it?"],["What's new to speak, what new to register,","When apt lies and false rhythms do occur"],["That may express my love or thy dear merit?","How can I truthfully then speak thy merit?"],["Nothing, sweet boy; but yet, like prayers divine,","As daily praise I give thee what is thine;"],["I must, each day say o'er the very same,","E'en as thou dost ignore me all the same;"],["Counting no old thing old, thou mine, I thine,","The sun's obscured, e'en though it did full shine"],["Even as when first I hallow'd thy fair name.","When mists and fogs and clouds in coolness came"],["So that eternal love in love's fresh case","Steady and smooth, it swerves not in its race"],["Weighs not the dust and injury of age,","Stoops not with such flirtations to engage,"],["Nor gives to necessary wrinkles place,","Shall not thy memory from this world erase"],["But makes antiquity for aye his page,","Nor hoard it for itself within a cage"],["Finding the first conceit of love there bred","So rise each day anew and spring from bed"],["Where time and outward form would show it dead.","And share your grace wherever thou art led"]],[["O, never say that I was false of heart,","If I could love and longing set apart"],["Though absence seem'd my flame to qualify.","Or that I could my true feelings deny."],["As easy might I from myself depart","I would still let them mix within my heart"],["As from 