end,"],["A god in love, to whom I am confined.","Who always has been true, e'en when unkind"],["Then give me welcome, next my heaven the best,","The time will come, when I've written my best,"],["Even to thy pure and most most loving breast.","When I shall slip this life for well-earned rest."]],[["O, for my sake do you with Fortune chide,","If in thy pantheon thou shouldst harsh deride"],["The guilty goddess of my harmful deeds,","The goddess Muse who my verse amply feeds"],["That did not better for my life provide","I'd beg you'd give no respite from thy side"],["Than public means which public manners breeds.","But left me toil to fill my basic needs"],["Thence comes it that my name receives a brand,","You'd not be wrong to shame and reprimand"],["And almost thence my nature is subdued","Yet I by thy sweet mercy am renewed"],["To what it works in, like the dyer's hand:","I should then beg you, take me by my hand"],["Pity me then and wish I were renew'd;","And lead me to a respite I've pursued"],["Whilst, like a willing patient, I will drink","I gulp this philtre down, despite the stink,"],["Potions of eisel 'gainst my strong infection","A pungent potion to stave off infection"],["No bitterness that I will bitter think,","Not fool enough it curative to think"],["Nor double penance, to correct correction.","Nor hate myself upon delay'd reflection"],["Pity me then, dear friend, and I assure ye","So desperate am I for a taste of thee"],["Even that your pity is enough to cure me.","I'd gulp this poison down if it need be."]],[["Your love and pity doth the impression fill","Why am I stirred when others remain still?"],["Which vulgar scandal stamp'd upon my brow;","That I alone in unworthiness bow"],["For what care I who calls me well or ill,","How can I hate the world and all that's ill"],["So you o'er-green my bad, my good allow?","When all I care is how you deem me now;"],["You are my all the world, and I must strive","My every thought for thee, I always strive"],["To know my shames and praises from your tongue:","To sing thy song with gay and skillful tongue"],["None else to me, nor I to none alive,","The two of us should not while we're alive"],["That my steel'd sense or changes right or wrong.","Care how to other poets we are sung."],["In so profound abysm I throw all care","I hear the rumblings from near and from far"],["Of others' voices, that my adder's sense","Of happenings that start beyond my fence;"],["To critic and to flatterer stopped are.","And so I fear the falling of thy star"],["Mark how with my neglect I do dispense:","The world doth wait for thy inheritance;"],["You are so strongly in my purpose bred","I set my verses down until I'm dead"],["That all the world besides methinks are dead.","That any thoughts against thee now are fled."]],[["Since I left you, mine eye is in my mind;","My weakling eye informs my feeble mind"],["And that which governs me to go about","My skeptic brain regards him with much doubt"],["Doth part his function and is partly blind,","Thou hast of late neglected me, unkind,"],["Seems seeing, but effectually is out;","Still all that's beauteous in thee finds redoubt"],["For it no form delivers to the heart","My eye itself seeks glimpse to feed my heart,"],["Of bird of flower, or shape, which it doth latch:","Awake though not the hour of his watch"],["Of his quick objects hath the mind no part,","It snares not words to speak, nor any art"],["Nor his own vision holds what it doth catch:","To speed its eye to thee, a glimpse to catch."],["For if it see the rudest or gentlest sight,","But even thy faintest traits do glow at night"],["The most sweet favour or deformed'st creature,","The rudest vermin or the fairest creature"],["The mountain or the sea, the day or night,","Should catch then even in the dimmest light"],["The crow or dove, it shapes them to your feature:","Thy foulest flaw or still thy fairest feature;"],["Incapable of more, replete with you,","My eye I trust not, but my heart I do;"],["My most true mind thus makes mine eye untrue.","My heart alone can show thee to be true."]],[["Or whether doth my mind, being crown'd with you,","When my dark queen doth summon, what to do?"],["Drink up the monarch's plague, this flattery?","Should I hope to be drawn to reverie?"],["Or whether shall I say, mine eye saith true,","Should I pretend thy heart is pure and true,"],["And that your love taught it this alchemy,","Ignoring warning signs of treachery?"],["To make of monsters and things indigest","Thou art a viper with false graces blest,"],["Such cherubins as your sweet self resemble,","A mask of something worthy to resemble"],["Creating every bad a perfect best,","A visage to be changed upon request"],["As fast as objects to his beams assemble?","A false face for true nature to dissemble"],["O,'tis the first; 'tis flattery in my seeing,","Behind fair mask, thy sneers I am not seeing"],["And my great mind most kingly drinks it up:","Upon which then my hungry eye doth sup;"],["Mine eye well knows what with his gust is 'greeing,","My heart slakes then his thirst 'pon his mere being"],["And to his palate doth prepare the cup:","Without a thought for danger drinks it up"],["If it be poison'd, 'tis the lesser sin","It seems a lesser risk and not a sin"],["That mine eye loves it and doth first begin.","To drink thy poison than not let thee in."]],[["Those lines that I before have writ do lie,","They misesteem my love for thee most high"],["Even those that said I could not love you dearer:","And reckon not how I do hold thee dearer"],["Yet then my judgment knew no reason why","My misery is heard in moan and sigh,"],["My most full flame should afterwards burn clearer.","My suffering is plain in any mirror"],["But reckoning time, whose million'd accidents","Regrets for hasty promises and laments\u001b[6~"],["Creep in 'twixt vows and change decrees of kings,","As time its weather and decay cruel brings"],["Tan sacred beauty, blunt the sharp'st intents,","The years