"If in your debt I willingly do fall"],["Wherein I should your great deserts repay,","It is a debt I will quite gladly pay"],["Forgot upon your dearest love to call,","My nights of longing leave me in thy thrall"],["Whereto all bonds do tie me day by day;","And unrewarded still at break of day."],["That I have frequent been with unknown minds","Know I've stood firm as oak while pine tree bends,"],["And given to time your own dear-purchased right","That I've born both spring's thaws and winter's bite"],["That I have hoisted sail to all the winds","I've suffered ocean swells and brutal winds"],["Which should transport me farthest from your sight.","And braved storms that blow all the day and night"],["Book both my wilfulness and errors down","And seen many a noble tree fall'n down"],["And on just proof surmise accumulate;","If I've lost favor and thou art irate"],["Bring me within the level of your frown,","Declare me dim, declare me but a clown,"],["But shoot not at me in your waken'd hate;","I pray you not my efforts to berate;"],["Since my appeal says I did strive to prove","My love for thee through words I hope to prove"],["The constancy and virtue of your love.","And by that proving strive to gain thy love"]],[["Like as, to make our appetites more keen,","When illness turns our healthy pallors green"],["With eager compounds we our palate urge,","And we pray to avoid a funeral dirge"],["As, to prevent our maladies unseen,","When in our illness final days are seen"],["We sicken to shun sickness when we purge,","We seek our souls to feed, bad humors purge;"],["Even so, being tuff of your ne'er-cloying sweetness,","When I did find my fruit sucked dry of sweetness"],["To bitter sauces did I frame my feeding","When subject to this world's unkindest feeding"],["And, sick of welfare, found a kind of meetness","A spectrum full to seek in its completeness"],["To be diseased ere that there was true needing.","A lustful wanting, an unhealthy needing;"],["Thus policy in love, to anticipate","How changed and wretched are things now of late,"],["The ills that were not, grew to faults assured","They've taken turns ironic and absurd"],["And brought to medicine a healthful state","My fortunes, so perverse and deviate,"],["Which, rank of goodness, would by ill be cured:","Do swerve like gyring flight of sickly bird;"],["But thence I learn, and find the lesson true,","No medicine returns a healthy hue:"],["Drugs poison him that so fell sick of you.","But Time alone will cure or kill, 'tis true."]],[["What potions have I drunk of Siren tears,","Should alchemy mix sweet love with bitter tear"],["Distill'd from limbecks foul as hell within,","Each element tempering with its dark twin"],["Applying fears to hopes and hopes to fears,","As one withdraws, the other draws then near"],["Still losing when I saw myself to win!","They complement and prove each other then."],["What wretched errors hath my heart committed,","'Tis travesty to find thy fair soul quitted"],["Whilst it hath thought itself so blessed never!","Beyond which mortal brain may endeavour"],["How have mine eyes out of their spheres been fitted","No rhyme can rhyme, no meter can be fitted,"],["In the distraction of this madding fever!","And my poor brain is stripped of all thoughts clever."],["O benefit of ill! now I find true","I find on singing of thee, pure and true,"],["That better is by evil still made better;","My words unstopped and flowing, never better."],["And ruin'd love, when it is built anew,","Someday my pen, to pay thy praises due,"],["Grows fairer than at first, more strong, far greater.","Shall find new strength that none shall ever fetter"],["So I return rebuked to my content","For now I find my quill split, dry, and bent:"],["And gain by ill thrice more than I have spent.","My verse exhausted and my talents spent"]],[["That you were once unkind befriends me now,","My urge to praise thee, post-betrayal now"],["And for that sorrow which I then did feel","Unnerves me, though it should my old wounds heal;"],["Needs must I under my transgression bow,","To this reversal I should need to bow"],["Unless my nerves were brass or hammer'd steel.","To make this switch in attitude feel real"],["For if you were by my unkindness shaken","Thy time with me I trust is happily taken,"],["As I by yours, you've pass'd a hell of time,","To waste thy fleeting hours would be a crime"],["And I, a tyrant, have no leisure taken","I bid thee from thy slumber to awaken"],["To weigh how once I suffered in your crime.","To see the sun and hear my song and rhyme"],["O, that our night of woe might have remember'd","We find ourselves by unkind world cruel-rendered"],["My deepest sense, how hard true sorrow hits,","Whilst Time us spares and memory still remits;"],["And soon to you, as you to me, then tender'd","Remembering the kindess thou has tendered"],["The humble slave which wounded bosoms fits!","I pay to thee in verse what thus befits;"],["But that your trespass now becomes a fee;","My debt to thee repaid in full shall be"],["Mine ransoms yours, and yours must ransom me.","I pay it gladly and revel in thee."]],[["'Tis better to be vile than vile esteem'd,","Tis better to be vile than be vile esteemed"],["When not to be receives reproach of being,","'Tis no shame, wicked to the wicked being;"],["And the just pleasure lost which is so deem'd","'Tis wrong to seek that you should be redeem'd"],["Not by our feeling but by others' seeing:","If villainy's called out from one's false-seeing."],["For why should others false adulterate eyes","Shall my foes who rejoice in my demise"],["Give salutation to my sportive blood?","Take shameful pride when spattered with my blood?"],["Or on my frailties why are frailer spies,","Why care about what others may despise,"],["Which in their wills count bad what I think good?","Those who can't tell pure water from base mud?"],["No, I am that I am, and they that level","Those jealous fools who in thy flaws do revel"],["At my abuses 