of a former sight.","My views of truth change not with the sun's flight"],["Our dates are brief, and therefore we admire","You offer nothing novel to inspire;"],["What thou dost foist upon us that is old,","I despair not as both of us grow old"],["And rather make them born to our desire","In verse I copy all things I admire"],["Than think that we before have heard them told.","And gild them to conceal the rot and mold."],["Thy registers and thee I both defy,","My words do not true memory belie"],["Not wondering at the present nor the past,","I do not falsely color moments past"],["For thy records and what we see doth lie,","Nor trying the true present to deny"],["Made more or less by thy continual haste.","As I now in my verse all strive to cast."],["This I do vow and this shall ever be;","So do thy worst, Death, there's no fear in me:"],["I will be true, despite thy scythe and thee.","I live through thee as thou shalt live through me"]],[["If my dear love were but the child of state,","Thy beauty I attribute not to Fate;"],["It might for Fortune's bastard be unfather'd'","Since Fortune's bastards often are unfathered;"],["As subject to Time's love or to Time's hate,","'Tis not for thee to miss the harvest, late,"],["Weeds among weeds, or flowers with flowers gather'd.","To lie in fields ungleaned and ungathered"],["No, it was builded far from accident;","Thy beauty is for the eternal meant;"],["It suffers not in smiling pomp, nor falls","It stands upright; it neither bows nor falls"],["Under the blow of thralled discontent,","In strong winds stands unbroken and unbent"],["Whereto the inviting time our fashion calls:","In sunlight bright it neither burns nor palls."],["It fears not policy, that heretic,","Like blooms in an ill garden, weak and sick,"],["Which works on leases of short-number'd hours,","Deceptively sweet in their final hours;"],["But all alone stands hugely politic,","Their stems are nought but scented candle's wick"],["That it nor grows with heat nor