 still will pluck thee back,","Grace thee with what thy foes envy and lack,"],["She keeps thee to this purpose, that her skill","Those cads who slander thee and wish thee ill"],["May time disgrace and wretched minutes kill.","Will prod thee, and won't rest 'til thou art still."],["Yet fear her, O thou minion of her pleasure!","The goddess who designed thee for her pleasure"],["She may detain, but not still keep, her treasure:","Did form thee as a dark alluring treasure"],["Her audit, though delay'd, answer'd must be,","The onus to praise thee is upon me,"],["And her quietus is to render thee.","This burden puts me in such reverie"],["(    )","Alas my words I find are at an end"],["(    )","[       ]"]],[["In the old age black was not counted fair,","The world sees not to deem thy darkness fair,"],["Or if it were, it bore not beauty's name;","Thy wan complexion some would sickly claim."],["But now is black beauty's successive heir,","The passions stirred by innocence laid bare,"],["And beauty slander'd with a bastard shame:","The lusciousness in darkness stirs the same;"],["For since each hand hath put on nature's power,","My dark lady's the lady of the hour,"],["Fairing the foul with art's false borrow'd face,","She crafted black of hair and fair of face,"],["Sweet beauty hath no name, no holy bower,","The darkness only magnifying her power"],["But is profaned, if not lives in disgrace.","And passion yet be stirred by her dark grace"],["Therefore my mistress' brows are raven black,","And thus her beauty is arrayed in black;"],["Her eyes so suited, and they mourners seem","A lovely shade seen only in a dream"],["At such who, not born fair, no beauty lack,","Thus tinted with a color others lack,"],["Slandering creation with a false esteem:","Her hair and eyes contrasting skin of cream"],["Yet so they mourn, becoming of their woe,","These gems set in her face, as dark as sloe,"],["That every tongue says beauty should look so.","Transformed from eyes of hawk to tragic doe."]],[["How oft, when thou, my music, music play'st,","I'd have thee with my worthy verse now graced"],["Upon that blessed wood whose motion sounds","But find it drown'd out by more earthy sounds"],["With thy sweet fingers, when thou gently sway'st","With vulgar celebrations we are faced;"],["The wiry concord that mine ear confounds,","The crowd moves gaily, the dancer twirls and bounds."],["Do I envy those jacks that nimble leap","The peasants caper round and eager leap"],["To kiss the tender inward of thy hand,","At hearing folk tunes from an untrained band"],["Whilst my poor lips, which should that harvest reap,","We sneak away and to the forest creep,"],["At the wood's boldness by thee blushing stand!","Like youthful lovers, creeping hand in hand;"],["To be so tickled, they would change their state","And so with tingling lips I stand and wait"],["And situation with those dancing chips,","To feel thee brush thy skin on legs and hips"],["O'er whom thy fingers walk with gentle gait,","Far from the crowd, we seek our lusts to sate,"],["Making dead wood more blest than living lips.","Caressing chin and cheeks and ears and lips"],["Since saucy jacks so happy are in this,","My darling, touching you is such sweet bliss"],["Give them thy fingers, me thy lips to kiss.","That I should shudder at the lightest kiss."]],[["The expense of spirit in a waste of shame","Those who you deem your jewels yet decay,"],["Is lust in action; and till action, lust","Still shining bright but showing signs of rust"],["Is perjured, murderous, bloody, full of blame,","They feign at being loyal and homage pay"],["Savage, extreme, rude, cruel, not to trust,","With vows of fealty but no cause for trust"],["Enjoy'd no sooner but despised straight,","If losing favor with thee were my fate,"],["Past reason hunted, and no sooner had","Cast off and scorned as a common cad"],["Past reason hated, as a swallow'd bait","I'd find myself subject to general hate"],["On purpose laid to make the taker mad;"