traying me, I do betray","My baser part stirs strongly, to my dismay,"],["My nobler part to my gross body's treason;","These carnal urges feel like vulgar treason"],["My soul doth tell my body that he may","My heart and soul would strip all flesh away"],["Triumph in love; flesh stays no father reason;","If possible, love thee beyond all reason"],["But, rising at thy name, doth point out thee","My rival gives poor praise, then doth claim thee"],["As his triumphant prize. Proud of this pride,","E'en serving thee and sleeping by thy side"],["He is contented thy poor drudge to be,","His morals for thy fleshly treats did flee,"],["To stand in thy affairs, fall by thy side.","Nobility thus soiled and cast aside."],["No want of conscience hold it that I call","I stand now noble, but do shameful call"],["Her 'love' for whose dear love I rise and fall.","To thee when I'mm spurred by my own lust's thrall"]],[["In loving thee thou know'st I am forsworn,","I can't for either of you bear much scorn"],["But thou art twice forsworn, to me love swearing,","Though dual betrayals I from thee am wearing:"],["In act thy bed-vow broke and new faith torn,","Though both of you did break a vow true sworn"],["In vowing new hate after new love bearing.","You break an oath that never did need swearing"],["But why of two oaths' breach do I accuse thee,","In breaking this vow, can I angry be"],["When I break twenty? I am perjured most;","For every crime of thine I twenty boast;"],["For all my vows are oaths but to misuse thee","Of being too like me I do accuse thee"],["And all my honest faith in thee is lost,","When of we three my sins total the most"],["For I have sworn deep oaths of thy deep kindness,","With this betrayal I think on your kindness"],["Oaths of thy love, thy truth, thy constancy,","And forgive thee when thou woundest me;"],["And, to enlighten thee, gave eyes to blindness,","On seeing thy misdeeds I do feign blindness"],["Or made them swear against the thing they see;","And still I praise thee when thy faults I see,"],["For I have sworn thee fair; more perjured I,","To speak the truth in verse I am too shy"],["To swear against the truth so foul a lie!","And seek to sing the truth in bitter lie."]],[["Cupid laid by his brand, and fell asleep:","When waking in a sylvan glade from sleep"],["A maid of Dian's this advantage found,","A nymph of Dian hearkened to the sound"],["And his love-kindling fire did quickly steep","Near to a river, flowing fast and deep"],["In a cold valley-fountain of that ground;","The little love god resting may be found"],["Which borrow'd from this holy fire of Love","In wand'ring wilderness, struck ill with love"],["A dateless lively heat, still to endure,","Many seek this spot to find their cure,"],["And grew a seething bath, which yet men prove","Praying for reprieve from up above"],["Against strange maladies a sovereign cure.","Fair Eros strings his bow so he shoots sure;"],["But at my mistress' eye Love's brand new-fired,","This visage seen and fair form thus admired,"],["The boy for trial needs would touch my breast;","By visions in my sleep I'm cursed and blessed"],["I, sick withal, the help of bath desired,","In dreams he comes e'en after I've retired,"],["And thither hied, a sad distemper'd guest,","Hoping end of malady stirred from rest,"],["But found no cure: the bath for my help lies","'Tis easy in Arcadia to surmise"],["Where Cupid got new fire--my mistress' eyes.","That even here the fear of death still lies."]],[["The little Love-god lying once asleep","The tiny love god, rousing from his sleep,"],["Laid by his side his heart-inflaming brand,","Doth stride forth with his little bow in hand"],["Whilst many nymphs that vow'd chaste life to keep","Thus armed, target to target he doth leap;"],["Came tripping by; but in her maiden hand","Dear Eros flits his wings across this land"],["The fairest votary took up that fire","He warms his arrows by a red-flamed fire"],["Which many legions of true hearts had warm'd;","Once it had kindled and the muscles warmed"],["And so the general of hot desire","And at this spot where he did once retire"],["Was sleeping by a virgin hand disarm'd.","A fire which would ever glow had form'd."],["This brand she quenched in a cool well by,","Neglected by the general reverie"],["Which from Love's fire took heat perpetual,","Yet this cooled not, not sudden nor eventual."],["Growing a bath and healthful remedy","This warm'd them 'gainst the cold and misery"],["For men diseased; but I, my mistress' thrall,","Pleasing e'en the soul with feeling sensual,"],["Came there for cure, and this by that I prove,","Thermodynamic rules sent from above;"],["Love's fire heats water, water cools not love.","Mere water cannot quench the fire of love."]]]